-- Yemen Army Clashes With Al-Qaeda Leave at Least 30 Dead
-- B y   M o h a m m e d   H a t e m
-- 2012-03-31T14:48:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-31/yemen-army-clashes-with-al-qaeda-leave-at-least-30-dead-1-.html
At least 17 Yemeni soldiers and 13
suspected al-Qaeda militants were killed in heavy fighting today
in the southern province of Lahj, a military official said.  The official, who requested anonymity because he was not
authorized to speak to the media, said by phone that the
militants attacked Brigade 119 in Millah district in Lahj,
killing 17 soldiers and wounding 15 others. He also said 13
militants were killed in the fighting, adding that the militants
briefly took control of the camp and the army used aircraft to
drive them out.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mohammed Hatem in Dubai at 
